    "headline": ") \"Braves\" (10). - 10 words.\n    *   *Idea",
    "subheadline": "New York Mets beats Atlanta Braves.",
    "lead_angle": "Marcus Semien cleared the left-field wall in the first inning to trigger a four-run avalanche, sending the New York Mets on their way to an 8-1 victory over the Atlanta Braves at Citi Field. Freddy Peralta stifled the Atlanta lineup to earn the victory, while Bryce Elder took the loss after his brief and bruising start on the mound.\n\nElder found trouble before he could record three outs in the opening frame, yielding a walk to Juan Soto before Semien lined his home run. Bo Bichette followed with a sharp double down the left-field line, and Brett Baty drove him home with a single to center to cap the early damage. That run support allowed Peralta to work with conviction, holding the Atlanta bats to just one hit over six frames of work.\n\nA.J. Ewing paced the New York attack, going 3-for-5 with a home run and two runs batted in to secure the victory. Soto also chipped in, collecting two hits and driving in two runs to keep the line moving in the later innings. This win tightens the race in the National League East, giving the Mets a crucial head-to-head edge against their division rivals as the summer heat begins to take hold.",
